<p id="notice"><%= notice %></p>

<p>
  <strong>Name:</strong>
  <%= @company.name %>
</p>

<p><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_company_path(@company) %></p>

<p>Here, given abilities, <b>:index</b> should always be <b class="green">authorized</b> for Project <b>1/2/3</b>.<br/>
<% if @company.name.include? 'owned' %>
As it's an <b>owned</b> company, <b>:custom_collection</b> should be <b class="green">authorized</b> for Project <b>1/2/3</b>.
<% else %>
As it's <b>not an owned</b> company, <b>:custom_collection</b> should be <b class="red">un-authorized</b> for Project <b>1/2/3</b>.
<% end %>
</p>
<% (1..3).each do |i| %>
<p>
<%= link_to "List projects #{i}", Rails.application.routes.url_helpers.send(:"company_project#{i}s_path", @company) %> |
<%= link_to "Custom collection #{i}", Rails.application.routes.url_helpers.send(:"custom_collection_company_project#{i}s_path", @company) %>
</p>
<% end %>
<p>
<% if @company.name.include? 'secret' %>
As it's a <b>secret</b> company, <b>:index and :custom_collection</b> actions should be <b class="red">un-authorized</b> for Project 4/5/6.
<% else %>
As it's <b>not a secret</b> company, <b>:index and :custom_collection</b> actions should be <b class="green">authorized</b> for Project 4/5/6.
<% end %>
</p>
<% (4..6).each do |i| %>
<p>
<%= link_to "List projects #{i}", Rails.application.routes.url_helpers.send(:"company_project#{i}s_path", @company) %> |
<%= link_to "Custom collection #{i}", Rails.application.routes.url_helpers.send(:"custom_collection_company_project#{i}s_path", @company) %>
</p>
<% end %>
<p>

<%= link_to 'Back', companies_path %>
</p>
